《'''被斬首的聖施洗者約翰'''》是一幅由意大利藝術家[[卡拉瓦喬|卡拉瓦喬]]繪製的[[油畫|油畫]]，是西方繪畫名作之一。<ref name="CaravaggioPomella2005">{{Cite book|last=Pomella|first=Andrea|title=Caravaggio: an artist through images|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=JDH4lOa8qRgC&pg=PA106|accessdate=28 June 2010|year=2005|publisher=ATS Italia Editrice|isbn=978-88-88536-62-0|page=106}}</ref> 這幅畫描繪的是[[施洗者約翰|施洗者約翰]]被斬首時，[[莎樂美|莎樂美]]在一旁用金盤子承接他的首級的場景。

==畫作==

畫中的另一個女性被認為是[[希羅底|希羅底]]（或者只是一個單純認為這項裁決是錯誤的旁觀者），<ref name="Harris2005">{{Cite book|last=Harris|first=Ann Sutherland|title=Seventeenth-century art & architecture|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=Xd0CuzsPYJcC&pg=PA48|accessdate=28 June 2010|year=2005|publisher=Laurence King Publishing|isbn=978-1-85669-415-5|page=48|archive-date=2016-05-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160519130552/https://books.google.com/books?id=Xd0CuzsPYJcC&pg=PA48|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Gaul2007">{{Cite book|last=Gaul|first=Simon|title=Malta Gozo & Comino, 4th|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=Fevix8jSqg0C&pg=PA109|accessdate=28 June 2010|date=1 October 2007|publisher=New Holland Publishers|isbn=978-1-86011-365-9|page=109|archive-date=2017-02-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170215051424/https://books.google.com/books?id=Fevix8jSqg0C&pg=PA109|dead-url=no}}</ref> 其他兩人分別是發佈斬首命令的獄卒和執行命令的劊子手。意大利很多藝術家對這個故事場景都很熟悉，但這並不像是受聖經啓發，而更多的是受《[[黃金傳說_(書)|黃金傳說]]》的影響。<ref name="Hibbard1985">{{Cite book|last=Hibbard|first=Howard|title=Caravaggio|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=SwLpTgpjAVYC&pg=PA228|accessdate=28 June 2010|date=5 March 1985|publisher=Westview Press|isbn=978-0-06-430128-2|page=228|archive-date=2017-02-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170215051429/https://books.google.com/books?id=SwLpTgpjAVYC&pg=PA228|dead-url=no}}</ref>

這幅畫是唯一有卡拉瓦喬簽名的畫作，簽名位於約翰喉嚨流出中的血中。<ref name="Rowland2005">{{Cite book|last=Rowland|first=Ingrid Drake|title=From heaven to Arcadia: the sacred and the profane in the Renaissance|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=yke1Kx4v9sYC&pg=PA163|accessdate=28 June 2010|year=2005|publisher=New York Review of Books|isbn=978-1-59017-123-3|page=163|archive-date=2017-02-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170224060311/https://books.google.com/books?id=yke1Kx4v9sYC&pg=PA163|dead-url=no}}</ref> 這幅畫中人物的大小都與真人相仿。<ref>Hibbard (1985), 232.</ref>

根據約翰·瓦里亞諾（John Varriano）在《卡拉瓦喬：現實主義藝術》 （''Caravaggio: the Art of Realism''）所說， 這幅畫的背景取材自馬爾他騎士團刑法典中所記載的一所監獄。<ref name="VarrianoCaravaggio2006">{{Cite book|last=Varriano|first=John L.|title=Caravaggio: the art of realism|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=YMhkLIxpOWkC&pg=PA116|accessdate=28 June 2010|year=2006|publisher=Penn State Press|isbn=978-0-271-02717-3|page=116|archive-date=2017-02-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170224060400/https://books.google.com/books?id=YMhkLIxpOWkC&pg=PA116|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==歷史==
[[File:CaravaggioSalomeLondon.jpg|thumb]]]]
[[File:CaravaggioSalomeMadrid.jpg|thumb]]]]
這幅畫於1608年完成於[[馬爾他|馬爾他]]，它是受[[馬爾他騎士團|馬爾他騎士團]]委託繪製的[[單幅祭壇畫|單幅祭壇畫]]，<ref name="CaravaggioPomella2005"/><ref>Varriano (2006), pp. 74, 116.</ref> 同時也是卡拉瓦喬繪製過的最大的單幅祭壇畫。<ref name="Patrick2007">{{Cite book|last=Patrick|first=James|title=Renaissance and Reformation|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=i6ZJlLHLPY8C&pg=PA194|accessdate=28 June 2010|year=2007|publisher=Marshall Cavendish|isbn=978-0-7614-7651-1|page=194|archive-date=2017-02-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170224060639/https://books.google.com/books?id=i6ZJlLHLPY8C&pg=PA194|dead-url=no}}</ref> 現在這幅畫依然懸掛在馬爾他的[[聖若望副主教座堂_(瓦萊塔)|聖若望副主教座堂]]，卡拉瓦喬本人之前也曾在此處受徵召而做了一段時間騎士，<ref name="Rowland2005"/><ref name="Patrick2007"/> 不過時間很短，最終還因為犯了罪行（罪行本身沒有被記錄下來）而被迫逃亡。<ref name="Gaul2007"/>

之後卡拉瓦喬還繪製了幾副與此畫相關的作品，現分別藏於[[國家美術館_(倫敦)|國家美術館]]和[[馬德里王宮|馬德里王宮]]。據信這兩幅畫其中之一（不確定）是卡拉瓦喬打算送與馬爾他騎士團團長[[阿洛夫·德·魏格納科特|阿洛夫·德·魏格納科特]]以解決自己被騎士團驅逐的問題的。<ref>Hibbard (1985), 249.</ref>

在1955年至1956年著名的[[羅馬|羅馬]]巡展之前，這幅畫於1950年代曾歷經多次修復，<ref>Hibbard (1985), p. 230.</ref>  然而仍然難逃嚴重損壞的命運，<ref name="HagenHagen2002">{{Cite book|last1=Hagen|first1=Rose-Marie|author2=Rainer Hagen|title=What great paintings say|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=aOzohrk8Mm8C&pg=PA216|accessdate=28 June 2010|date=2 February 2002|publisher=Taschen|isbn=978-3-8228-2100-8|page=216|archive-date=2014-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140111230349/http://books.google.com/books?id=aOzohrk8Mm8C&pg=PA216|dead-url=no}}</ref> 不過也正是因這些修復工作使得卡拉瓦喬的簽名出現在了世人眼前。<ref name="Hammill2002">{{Cite book|last=Hammill|first=Graham L.|title=Sexuality and Form: Caravaggio, Marlowe, and Bacon|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=UhcWIlk-67IC&pg=PA95|accessdate=28 June 2010|date=15 December 2002|publisher=University of Chicago Press|isbn=978-0-226-31519-5|page=95|archive-date=2014-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140111231451/http://books.google.com/books?id=UhcWIlk-67IC&pg=PA95|dead-url=no}}</ref> 該簽名引起了許多爭議，因為一些學者認為這個簽名是''f. Michelang.o'' （''f'' 為卡拉瓦喬在兄弟中的排行），<ref>Warwick (2006), p. 15.</ref> 而不是更常見的說法：''I, Caravaggio, did this'' ——即可能是在懺悔1606年畫家殺死Ranuccio Tomassoniin的罪行——該事件也直接導致卡拉瓦喬逃出羅馬。<ref name="Pencak2002">{{Cite book|last=Pencak|first=William|title=The films of Derek Jarman|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=CZiBbPphZEwC&pg=PA70|accessdate=28 June 2010|date=October 2002|publisher=McFarland|isbn=978-0-7864-1430-7|page=70|archive-date=2014-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140111225947/http://books.google.com/books?id=CZiBbPphZEwC&pg=PA70|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Peachment2003">{{Cite book|last=Peachment|first=Christopher|title=Caravaggio|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=N9UyHvUxDVcC&pg=PA168|accessdate=28 June 2010|date=6 May 2003|publisher=Macmillan|isbn=978-0-312-31448-4|page=168}}</ref><ref name="Jackson1995">{{Cite book|last=Jackson|first=Earl|title=Strategies of deviance: studies in gay male representation|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=o2ZfhAYmNoYC&pg=PA81|accessdate=28 June 2010|year=1995|publisher=Indiana University Press|isbn=978-0-253-33115-1|page=81|archive-date=2014-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140111231133/http://books.google.com/books?id=o2ZfhAYmNoYC&pg=PA81|dead-url=no}}</ref>

